reviews_data.review_text:
I’ve been meaning to write this with you for a while so here goes… I grew up the daughter of Detroit entrepreneurs who owned what they call party stores.
Savvy provisions brought an awesome concept to the perfect location on the Rail Trail where hundreds of people walk and jog! It is a spot surrounded by apartments. This convenience store is ideal especially since there’s too much traffic in SouthEnd if you have to drive someplace to pick up a little something that you can easily get here!

I love the fact that they have a good amount of organic and natural options especially for cleaning. Lots of seating to just hang out for a bit. My daddy would have loved this concept!

Check out Savi Provisions!

Happy Exploring!

Josephine Local Guide
Best store to shop in Charlotte area.

I'm a frequent shopper and a Black American woman, same color as the worker ironically, I get stared down the whole shopping experience each time by the tall bald Indian/Pakistani man. People really need to learn about how to treat Americans when coming here from another country. I promise you the same people you do NOT stereotype are the main ones that actually steal, speaking from someone who has worked in a large business when I was younger. I will not return here, I would rather support other businesses with my hard earned money.
Upscale convenience store with a great beer selection and stuff on-tap too. Location is fantastic and the workers are great.
Good place for convenience but fix your freezer. Ice cream freezer isn’t working and still selling. People will get sick.
Really great freshly made sandwiches. Cuban sandwich was awesome.

One of the more underrated gems in south end. I stop in here for a water/gatorade every time I walk the rail trail. Staff is friendly and welcoming, never annoyed if need to use restroom. Dogs welcomed and if you have no shirt on while walking/running on trail, they’ll let it slide.
Excelente sitio

We spotted this cute convenience store as we're walking around South End looking for something. Mrs. K. saw the candy display and now we're in here and looking.

Wine, wine, wine. So much wine. Chilled and shelf. And beer for miles. Yes, and snacks and candies and deli.

Friendly folks and yes, a challenge to find this place if you're not on foot.
Such a hidden gem in south end. They have great prices and the nicest workers.
Ordered for the first time on doordash.  2 sandwiches, both were disgusting  and tasted like rotten fish. ( no fish in either)

Was recently walking the rail trail and stumbled upon this new hidden gem. I had the turkey sandwich, and my husband had the tuna melt (which he said was one of the best he's ever had). It was so nice to be able to sit outside on their patio and a tasty lunch, without breaking the bank. Will definitely be back!
Veggie sandwich was bomb! Great service too! Try it out!

Bought 2 boxes of crackers here today and both were expired. Unfortunately we didn’t realize until after we started eating them. The one box had been expired since October of last year.

Please do a better job of checking your merchandise before putting out to customers.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Really sorry for that. we will do our best and we can refund it

reviews_data.review_text: Really great place they have really good sandwiches must check it out

Truly awesome sandwiches in a relaxed and very pleasant space. The gluten free bread is also really good if you have an allergy. We decided to give the place a try and ended up coming back 3 times in 10 days!
The sandwiches are fantastic! In our opinion, MUCH better than sandwiches at nearby places like Rhino or Common Market. The outdoor seating is really nice, too. This is our new go-to lunch spot!
Very friendly and helpful.  Took extra steps on Thanksgiving Day to find an item I needed and priced fairly.

Great sandwiches, friendly workers. I appreciate them doing an extra step for me when ordering my sub, which is atypical elsewhere. It’s a bit pricey for what it is, but I feel that it’s expected for the area so I’m not knocking them for it.

Love their beer choices too, fully stocked on stuff that’s hard to find elsewhere. Grocery had a lot that I didn’t expect too. If I lived here instead of working nearby I’d shop here.

This is my weekly lunch spot.
You need to go here! The guys working there are so kind. The food is great and they have huge wine and beer selection!
It says it's open until 12am but it's not. Went at 10:55 on Thursday and the store was locked up with the worker telling me he has to leave
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry for inconvenient. Please check out our new hours on Google

reviews_data.review_text: overpriced compare to regular grocery store. Saffron Road meal cost $9.99 at other places you can get  that for under $4.38-$5.49. Had a small selection. Organic valley gallon milk $9.99 more than a grocery store avoid this store unless if you have lots of $$
This place is a great addition to the area! The sandwiches are delicious. The staff are super friendly and welcoming. We live nearby and having this place near us is awesome. Super convenient!

Great Provisions Store in SouthEnd by the Sycamore Brewery, nice selections of products, patio is pet friendly and amazing Gourmet Sandwiches!
Open Late, which makes it a great place to hang out.

Chilling @ Savi Provisions.... SouthEnd Charlotte NC.
Great place by Sycamore Brewery and across from Trolley Barn.

Must try their Gourmet Sandwiches
Great sandwich... Excellent service
Unique gourmet sandwich experience.
I love this little grocery store which just opened up at The Line! They have all the essentials, tasty snacks, and fresh food! They’re also open late, which makes it a great late-night place to stop.
